Vodacom announced today that it will implement a below-inflation average price increase on selected packages on 1 April 2019. No specific details on the price increases were provided at the time, and the announcement was made as part of a statement on new out-of-bundle (OOB) data rates. The network has now informed customers about which packages will be affected, and created a webpage that details the new pricing. “With effect from the 1st April 2019, your monthly subscription and certain value added services will be increasing,” said Vodacom. “We have ensured that the price increase is below inflation in order to ensure our customers stay connected at the best value.” The tables below detail Vodacom’s new pricing. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-297696" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-months.png" alt="" width="640" height="641" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-months.png 1336w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-months-399x400.png 399w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-months-768x769.png 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-months-429x430.png 429w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-months-1200x1202.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-297698" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/24-months.png" alt="" width="640" height="646" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/24-months.png 1334w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/24-months-396x400.png 396w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/24-months-768x775.png 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/24-months-426x430.png 426w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/24-months-1200x121